replies.body:
there are so many things that applies to. My first lvl 30 match, i tried to take varus mid....i got flamed so hard. A few months later hes all the rage in mid on the pro scene and if you varus mid in low elo your a try hard sheep.

Urgot...nobody plays urgot hes trash. Oh snap lpl urgot mid? better na lcs urgot mid ASAP!! now urgot mid is good....they stopped playing urgot mid, so now urgot mid is bad again and nobody plays urgot.

yesterday i saw lucian top in EU LCS....i cant even begin to predict what will happen next{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-popcorn}}

what people think about the champion strongly affects how well their whole team does, not just the champion themselves. if you see a teammate playing {{champion:122}} for example, you're like "yea he's got a strong champ we're gunna do good" which makes YOU do good, and makes the rest of your team do good, while the {{champion:122}} also does good cuz he's sitting there like "hurr durr {{champion:122}} OP" and your opponents are going "oh great we have to deal with a {{champion:122}} this is gunna suck" but i bet you anything if you somehow got it into peoples heads that {{champion:122}} was a weak champion, all those effects would be flipped on their heads. {{champion:122}} playrate would plummet, his winrate would drop, his opponents would play better and {{champion:122}} and his teammates would play just a little bit worse.

tl;dr: complaining about a champion being OP actually makes them more OP {{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}} 
PS: you can sub every {{champion:122}} for {{champion:114}} or {{champion:24}} or whoever you want
